BLUE SEA
EXPORT IMPORT
BLUE SEA EXPORT IMPORT S.R.L. from Focsani, Romania is looking for U.S.A. suppliers and clients to prevent the spread of communism. Contact us via WhatsApp, Telegram, Messenger, Letter or E-mail. Thank you !
On PC / Laptop: Press Ctrl and plus key (+) to increase font size or Press Ctrl and minus key (-) to decrease font size
To save the catalog so you can see it offline on PC / Laptop: Press Ctrl and letter S
On Smartphone / Tablet: Pinch to zoom. Touch the screen with two fingers. Move your fingers away from one another, while touching the screen.

If you don't understand the Google Translation, request help from someone who understands English.

Important info for suppliers and clients:

Minimum order For buying products between European Union Companies: 4000 EUR
Minimum order For Non-EU Companies: 100000 EUR
We accept bank transfer only. No barter or cash or cards accepted.

To prevent money laundering and to combat terrorism, before you sign the commission contract, as client company you must sign a GDPR data processing agreement and you must justify the source of funds (SOF) with documents.

Elderly people must have mental health certificates before signing any contract. It is proof they have the mental capacity / discernment / legal competence to sign documents. Young people must be over 21 years old.

BLUE SEA EXPORT IMPORT S.R.L. employees must allow any Person, Institution, NGO, or Company to view or capture images and videos of all public documents, including public price lists. If employees try to sabotage you, report them immediately via email or social media. Such employees will be immediately terminated ( fired ). We will also send you the documents ASAP in PDF or JPG format via email.

A. We do not sell or offer services to private persons - individuals. ( We are a B2B company )
B. We do not store products, we buy the products from suppliers after clients sign contracts and send payment.
C. We want clients to get the products fresh so we can also reduce energy and storage costs.
D. Do not manufacture products without a contract. We will only buy fresh products from suppliers.

    How To Buy Guide For Companies

    Edit the products list

    You can use LibreOffice Calc, Excel, Word

    ( e.g. BSEI-100119-0001 x 1000 tonnes )


    All suppliers and clients must edit and sign the Declaration of Compliance with BLUE SEA EXPORT IMPORT S.R.L. Principles before we do any business.

    1. Send products list via E-mail or Telegram or Postal Letter [ in the letter, include also your contact info ]

    2. When you send the list, include also your [ company public documents + declaration of compliance ] and [ technical specifications - quality parameters - datasheets - technical drawings ].

    3. We verify your company public documents

    4. We verify if products can be sent to you

    5. We request prices from suppliers

    6. We select the best prices from suppliers

    7. We send you the best prices


    If you're happy with the prices

    8. We prepare commission contract clauses, shipping, itinerary and export-import procedures for non-EU countries.

    9. The commission fee is 10% out of Total costs. Total costs you will see in the estimated costs annex of the contract.

    10. We and the banks check all the documents. If documents are ok, we sign the contract. After we send you the proforma invoice, and your company has to transfer the payment via TT / Money Order ( Bank Transfer ).

    11. We start the delivery process after payment is confirmed, we also send you a copy of the legal invoice - payment receipt.

    12. Suppliers will be paid after you inspect the products when they arrive at your location and after you sign the handover documents. ( Why ? Due to the fact suppliers are sneaky, they use sweet talk to get contracts, and after they do bad work or deliver junk products. )

    13. If the products are not according to the contract terms, we will refund you the money minus expenses included in the contract.

    14. If suppliers do not respect the contract terms, they get zero payment.


    Example of Total costs for Non-EU Countries:

    Suppliers scouting price on invoice ( bus-plane tickets, food, room rent, visa etc ) : €1000
    Packaging design, label design, trademark registration in USA price on invoice: €3000
    Raw materials Laboratory analysis price on invoice: €500
    Documents translation and lawyers price on invoice: €500
    Romania and USA import-export licences and government authorizations price on invoice: €500
    Almost 10-15year documents archiving price on invoice: €500
    Product 1 manufacturing price on invoice: 100pcs x €10 = €1000
    Product 2 manufacturing price on invoice: 1000pcs x €10 = €10000
    Product 3 manufacturing price on invoice: 100pcs x €10 = €1000
    Quality control finite products laboratory analysis fees: €1500
    Products compliance with EU and USA standards ( e.g. CE marking documents ) price on invoice: €5000
    Certificate of Origin price on invoice: €500
    40FT Container Rent Focsani - New York price on invoice: €3000
    Warehousing, Logistics, labeling and packaging price on invoice: €5000
    Transport Focsani - New York price on invoice: €10000
    Export Insurance price on invoice: €1000
    Romania and USA Customs brokers price on invoice: €10000
    VAT and Customs Taxes invoice: €10000
    Accounting price on invoice: €5000
    Romania and USA Products security and monitoring price on invoice: €5000
    Corporate intelligence price on invoice: €3000
    Communication and IT services price on invoice ( e.g. Romania to USA phone calls ): €500
    Transport New York port - Syracuse Warehouse price on invoice: €1500
    Banking fees cost on invoice: €4000
    Total Costs: €83000
    BLUE SEA EXPORT IMPORT SRL 10% commission fee : €83000 * 0.1 = €8300
    Total without Romanian 19% VAT: €91300
    Total Romanian 19% VAT: €17347
    Total your company needs to send to BLUE SEA EXPORT IMPORT SRL: €91300 + €17347 = €108647

    For business between EU companies there is no export-import procedures ! ( You pay VAT only ! e.g. Products manufactured in Spain sent to companies in Finland )

    Example of Total costs for business between EU Countries:

    Product 1 price on invoice: 100pcs x €10 = €1000
    Product 2 price on invoice: 1pcs x €1000 = €1000
    Product 3 price on invoice: 5pcs x €200 = €1000
    Product 4 price on invoice: 20pcs x €50 = €1000
    Quality control finite products laboratory analysis fees: €150
    Transport Focsani - Paris Warehouse price on invoice: €300
    Banking fees cost on invoice: €50
    Total Costs: €4500
    BLUE SEA EXPORT IMPORT SRL 10% commission fee : €4500 * 0.1 = €450
    Total without Romanian 19% VAT: €4950
    Total Romanian 19% VAT: €940.5
    Total your company needs to send to BLUE SEA EXPORT IMPORT SRL: €4950 + €940.5 = €5890.5

    and other expenses ( unknown costs are called systematic risk )


    When products arrive at your Warehouse, you or your legal company representative inspect the products. For all products according to the commission contract, your company representative signs the handover documents and BLUE SEA EXPORT IMPORT SRL transfers payments to suppliers involved. Task completed !

    61211 - Wholesale trade services on a fee or contract basis, of grains and oilseeds and oleaginous fruits, seeds and animal feed Open
    Download as PDF

    Note: For all products in this section, your company has to send the technical specs / quality parameters

    Note: Your company must be authorized to buy these products. ( We do not accept requests from speculators )

    Note: Suppliers must have accredited laboratory test results as proof of safety issued by authorized government agencies for all products. ( Private laboratory test results are not accepted. If the products are poisoned intentionally, it's an act of war ! )

    Note: The client company must specify the variaty they need from official plant variety databases-catalogues ( No GMO allowed ! )

    Note: The client company must specify the degree of ripeness for each product.

    Note: The client company must specify in advance, before harvest, the period when they need these products. ( Some plants are seasonal, some are all year round e.g. check harvest calendars )

    Note: The seeds used by farmers must be certified.

    Note: The water used to irrigate or to clean the products must not be contaminated. The suppliers must have document proof that the water used is clean. The water must come from sustainable sources.

    Note: To farm the land, suppliers can use [ hand tools ] or [ horse and plow ] or [ high-tech equipment ]. The tools and equipment must be environmentally friendly and energy efficient. Governments around the world offer many subsidies and financing to farmers.

    Note: Suppliers must figure out solutions for how to farm the products without using pesticides. There are many farmers around the world that overspray crops with pesticides. Where possible, avoid pesticides.

    61212 - Wholesale trade services on a fee or contract basis, of flowers and plants Open
    Download as PDF

    Note: For all products in this section, your company has to send the technical specs / quality parameters

    Note: Your company must be authorized to buy these products. ( We do not accept requests from speculators )

    Note: Suppliers must have accredited laboratory test results as proof of safety issued by authorized government agencies for all products. ( Private laboratory test results are not accepted. If the products are poisoned intentionally, it's an act of war ! )

    Note: In European Union most live plants need a plant passport before they are put on the market

    Note: The client company must specify the variaty they need from official plant variety databases-catalogues ( No GMO allowed ! )

    Note: The client company must specify the degree of ripeness for each product.

    Note: The client company must specify in advance, before harvest, the period when they need these products. ( Some plants are seasonal, some are all year round e.g. check harvest calendars )

    Note: The seeds used by farmers must be certified.

    Note: The water used to irrigate or to clean the products must not be contaminated. The suppliers must have document proof that the water used is clean. The water must come from sustainable sources.

    Note: To farm the land, suppliers can use [ hand tools ] or [ horse and plow ] or [ high-tech equipment ]. The tools and equipment must be environmentally friendly and energy efficient. Governments around the world offer many subsidies and financing to farmers.

    Note: Suppliers must figure out solutions for how to farm the products without using pesticides. There are many farmers around the world that overspray crops with pesticides. Where possible, avoid pesticides.

    Note: For all products in class [ 0195 ], your company has to send the technical specs / quality parameters

    Note: Your company must be authorized to buy these products. ( We do not accept requests from speculators )

    Note: Suppliers must have accredited laboratory test results as proof of quality

    Note: TSNR must be accompanied by a test certificate, issued by the competent authorities of the producing country, specifying the grade, specifications and test results of the rubber.

    Note: TSR = Technically Specified Rubber

    Note: e.g. 3 - 3L = both grade L and grade 3L and all grades between L and 3L, is considered to be grade 3L.

    Note: The client company must specify the variaty they need from official plant variety databases-catalogues ( No GMO allowed ! )

    Note: The seeds used by farmers must be certified.

    Note: The water used to irrigate or to clean the products must not be contaminated. The suppliers must have document proof that the water used is clean. The water must come from sustainable sources.

    Note: To farm the land, suppliers can use [ hand tools ] or [ horse and plow ] or [ high-tech equipment ]. The tools and equipment must be environmentally friendly and energy efficient. Governments around the world offer many subsidies and financing to farmers.

    Note: Suppliers must figure out solutions for how to farm the products without using pesticides. There are many farmers around the world that overspray crops with pesticides. Where possible, avoid pesticides.

    Note: For all products in group [ 022 ], [ 023 ] and class [ 0291 ] your company has to send the technical specs / quality parameters

    Note: Your company must be authorized to buy these products. ( We do not accept requests from speculators )

    Note: Suppliers must have accredited laboratory test results as proof of safety issued by authorized government agencies for all products. ( Private laboratory test results are not accepted. If the products are poisoned intentionally, it's an act of war ! )

    Note: Suppliers for products in group [ 022 ], [ 023 ] and class [ 0291 ] must be authorized by food safety organizations, they must have proof of HACCP plan or HACCP accredited certificate

    Note: Some of the products in group [ 022 ], [ 023 ] and class [ 0291 ] must be pasteurized or sterilized and packaged according to food safety standards in recyclable or biodegradable food grade packaging

    Note: Frozen* means between -20 and -18° C, Cold* means between 2 and 4° C, Cool* means between 8 and 15° C, Room temperature* means between 15 and 20° C

    Note: The relative humidity (RH) must be under or equal to maximum allowed by exporter-importer governments, the products must be transported and stored according to manufacturer's instructions

    Note: Exporting - importing meat and animal byproducts is very complex. e.g. Only a few countries are allowed to import meat and animal byproducts inside the EU

    Note: We do not accept suppliers from regions with disease outbreaks. ( That means if you have diseases like Covid, Ebola virus, Swine flu, Mad Cow disease in your region we will not accept any meat or animal origin products from your company, even if your government tells us there is no problem, we must verify. )

    Note: For all products in class [ 0294 ] your company has to send the technical specs / quality parameters

    Note: Your company must be authorized to buy these products. ( We do not accept requests from speculators )

    Note: Suppliers must have accredited laboratory test results as proof of safety issued by authorized government agencies for all products. ( Private laboratory test results are not accepted. If the products are poisoned intentionally, it's an act of war ! )

    Note: For all products in class [ 0294 ], suppliers must have animal origin by-products safety documents

    Note: Fibers from cloned animals are not accepted

    Note: The animal shearer should sober and professional. No amatures should be allowed to shear the animals. Fibers from wounded animals are not accepted.

    Note: Suppliers must have traceability documents for all the products they used to treat the animals for lice, flies, maggots, mites, scab and other parasites.

    Note: Suppliers must have origin documents for all the products. ( e.g. It's forbidden to export goat hair from a region that has Ebola virus epidemic )

    Note: Before we buy the products, we must verify if suppliers use child labor, if they respect work labor laws, if suppliers pay salaries on time and so on.

    Note: Suppliers should use natural non-toxic insect repellents to counter damage from insects. ( e.g. Lavender and/or thyme herbal sachets )

    Note: The client company must specify the grading system, most countries have their own grading methods.

    Note: The fibers must be from the same breeds and it must have same color. No mixed colors and/or breeds and/or crossbreeds fibers are permited. ( Do not mix the fibers ! )

    Note: The fibers must be from same region of the animal. ( e.g. Wool from the belly region of the animal must not be mixed with lower quality wool from around the tail )

    Note: The fibers must have similar length. The suppliers must not mix long fibers with short fibers.

    Note: The suppliers must not try to fake wool, animal hair, silk or other expensive natural fibers. The suppliers must not mix wool with goat hair or dog hair or synthetic fibers and so on.

    Note: The products must have recyclable protective packaging against heat, sunlight, moisture and insects.

    Note: Wool and animal hair must be shorn.

    Note: The products must be labeled and baled according to client company specifications with recyclable and eco-friendly materials.

    Note: The practice of mulesing and treating animals with liquid nitrogen is forbbiden. The animals must not be mistreated. The animals must be well taken care of.

    Note: Suppliers must not brand the animals. The owners should use ear tags.

    Note: Suppliers must be washed and clean when they will shear the animals so they do not contaminate the products. No dogs allowed near the shearing area.

    Note: Suppliers must have accredited laboratory test results as proof of safety issued by authorized government agencies for all products. ( Private laboratory test results are not accepted. If the products are poisoned intentionally, it's an act of war ! )

    Note: Plants have many varieties, check plant variety catalogues, databases & information systems

    Note: The client company must specify the variaty they need from official plant variety databases-catalogues ( No GMO allowed ! )

    Note: The client company must specify the degree of ripeness for each product.

    Note: The client company must specify in advance, before harvest, the period when they need these products. ( Some plants are seasonal, some are all year round e.g. check harvest calendars )

    Note: The seeds used by farmers must be certified.

    Note: The water used to irrigate or to clean the products must not be contaminated. The suppliers must have document proof that the water used is clean. The water must come from sustainable sources.

    Note: To farm the land, suppliers can use [ hand tools ] or [ horse and plow ] or [ high-tech equipment ]. The tools and equipment must be environmentally friendly and energy efficient. Governments around the world offer many subsidies and financing to farmers.

    Note: Suppliers must figure out solutions for how to farm the products without using pesticides. There are many farmers around the world that overspray crops with pesticides. Where possible, avoid pesticides.

    Note: Suppliers must have accredited laboratory test results as proof of safety issued by authorized government agencies for all products. ( Private laboratory test results are not accepted. If the products are poisoned intentionally, it's an act of war ! )

    Note: Products in group [ 213 ], [ 214 ] must be pasteurized or sterilized and packaged according to food safety standards in recyclable or biodegradable food grade packaging

    Note: Frozen* means between -20 and -18° C, Cold* means between 0 and 4° C, Cool* means between 8 and 15° C, Room temperature* means between 15 and 20° C

The brine is a solution of potable water and food-grade salt (CXS 150-1985) with zero additives. Supplies must also have document proof that the water is "drinking - potable water". Suppliers can get the public drinking water lab test from the local water company or from the Mayor's office. When the food agency of the country where the products are imported tests the brine and if they discover that the water is not drinking water, the supplier will not get payed and his products will be confiscated and destroyed. All suppliers must have legal documents proof that shows their products are safe.If the border guards consider that the olives are cured, they will classify the goods as 200570

Supplies must also have document proof that the water is "drinking - potable water". Suppliers can get the public drinking water lab test from the local water company or from the Mayor's office. When the food agency of the country where the products are imported tests the brine and if they discover that the water is not drinking water, the supplier will not get payed and his products will be confiscated and destroyed. All suppliers must have legal documents proof that shows their products are safe.

    61222 - Wholesale trade services on a fee or contract basis, of dairy products, edible oils and fats Open
    Download as PDF

    Note: For all products in group [ 215 ], [ 216 ], [ 219 ], [ 221 ], [ 222 ], your company has to send the technical specs / quality parameters

    Note: Your company must be authorized to buy these products. ( We do not accept requests from speculators )

    Note: Suppliers must have accredited laboratory test results as proof of safety issued by authorized government agencies for all products. ( Private laboratory test results are not accepted. If the products are poisoned intentionally, it's an act of war ! )

    Note: Products in group [ 221 ], [ some products in 222 ] must be pasteurized or sterilized and packaged according to food safety standards in recyclable or biodegradable food grade packaging

    Note: Suppliers for products in this group must be authorized by food safety organizations, they must have proof of HACCP plan or HACCP accredited certificate

    Note: Frozen* means between -20 and -18° C, Cold* means between 0 and 4° C, Cool* means between 8 and 15° C, Room temperature* means between 15 and 20° C

    Note: The relative humidity (RH) must be under or equal to maximum allowed by exporter-importer governments, the products must be transported and stored according to manufacturer's instructions

    Note: Exporting - importing meat and animal byproducts is very complex. e.g. Only a few countries are allowed to import meat and animal byproducts inside the EU

    Note: We do not accept suppliers from regions with disease outbreaks. ( That means if you have diseases like Covid, Ebola virus, Swine flu, Mad Cow disease in your region we will not accept any meat or animal origin products from your company, even if your government tells us there is no problem, we must verify. )

    Explanatory note for BSEI-040610, BSEI-040640, BSEI-040690: Company client - Wait a minute, why should i buy cheese from Europe ? i can make my own European cheese. I just need the recipe. To obtain the same taste, you need the grass, the animals, the rennet, the water, the air from these countries, also the skilled workers. Geographical indications establish intellectual property rights for specific products, whose qualities are specifically linked to the area of production.

    61223 - Wholesale trade services on a fee or contract basis, of meat, poultry and game Open
    Download as PDF

    Note: For all products in this section, your company has to send the technical specs / quality parameters

    Note: Your company must be authorized to buy these products. ( We do not accept requests from speculators )

    Note: Suppliers must have accredited laboratory test results as proof of safety issued by authorized government agencies for all products. ( Private laboratory test results are not accepted. If the products are poisoned intentionally, it's an act of war ! )

    Note: Suppliers for products in this section must be authorized by food safety organizations, they must have proof of HACCP plan or HACCP accredited certificate

    Note: Some of the products in this section must be pasteurized or sterilized and packaged according to food safety standards in recyclable or biodegradable food grade packaging

    Note: Frozen* means between -20 and -18° C, Cold* means between 2 and 4° C, Cool* means between 8 and 15° C, Room temperature* means between 15 and 20° C

    Note: The relative humidity (RH) must be under or equal to maximum allowed by exporter-importer governments, the products must be transported and stored according to manufacturer's instructions

    Note: Exporting - importing meat and animal byproducts is very complex. e.g. Only a few countries are allowed to import meat and animal byproducts inside the EU

    Note: We do not accept suppliers from regions with disease outbreaks. ( That means if you have disease like Covid, Ebola virus, Swine flu, Mad Cow disease in your region we will not accept any meat or animal origin products from your company, even if your government tells us there is no problem, we must verify. )

    Note: For all products in this category you must have documents that you raised, feed, slaughter, proccesed the animals according to international food safety - food hygiene - biosecurity standards. The animals can be slaughter and stunned or the client company must send their own butchers to slaughter the animals according to their religios believes e.g. Kosher, Halal and so on. Universal Declaration of Human Rights Article 18 - Everyone has the right to freedom of thought, conscience and religion.

    Note: We do not accept meat from sick or infected animals, animals allowed to eat garbage, abused or bruised or injured animals, newly born, pregnant animals, animals with calfs under 1 year, animals with high fat deposits, stressed animals, uncastrated male animals, castrated under 4 months male animals, not well rested animals during the 24-hour period before slaughter, animals handled with electric prodders, animals living in unhygienic and overcrowded conditions, live animals not transported in clean-disinfected-washed-ventilated specialized vehicles, live animals transported in overcrowded vehicles, live animals transported more then 50-100km from place of origin.

    Note: The meat must be washed only with potable water, the meat should not have blood marks and must be clean, the meat must not have any foreign smell, the meat must not have broken bones, the meat must not be bruised, the meat must not be discolored, the meat must have characteristic color and so on, the meat must have the mandatory food safety and legal documents according to the international legislation and national legislation of each country.

    Note: Suppliers must eviscerate and clean the products with potable water, before they put them on scale to be weighted. They will not be payed for the eviscerated content - impurities.

    Note: Suppliers must have contracts with authorised companies to buy and/or to dispose the eviscerated content - impurities.

    Note: Suppliers must have documents evidence that the products do not contain antibiotics, parasites - pathogens, heavy metals, toxic chemicals.

    Note: Suppliers must have documents evidence that the products are not radioactive and that they do not come from contaminated areas like Chernobyl.

    Note: The products must be graded according to importer's country legislation and client needs.

    Note: Suppliers are not allowed to mix fresh products with old and/or spoiled products.

    Note: Meat is considered a biological weapon. Before we release any payment for these products, we want the legal representative of the supplier, his wife, his kids and his family to cook and eat a meat sample from the same lot that is shipped to clients around the world.

    61224 - Wholesale trade services on a fee or contract basis, of fish and other seafood Open
    Download as PDF

    Note: For all products in this section, your company has to send the technical specs / quality parameters

    Note: Your company must be authorized to buy these products. ( We do not accept requests from speculators )

    Note: Suppliers must have accredited laboratory test results as proof of safety issued by authorized government agencies for all products. ( Private laboratory test results are not accepted. If the products are poisoned intentionally, it's an act of war ! )

    Note: Suppliers for products in this section must be authorized by food safety organizations, they must have proof of HACCP plan or HACCP accredited certificate

    Note: Some of the products in this section must be pasteurized or sterilized and packaged according to food safety standards in recyclable or biodegradable food grade packaging

    Note: Frozen* means between -20 and -18° C, Cold* means between 2 and 4° C, Cool* means between 8 and 15° C, Room temperature* means between 15 and 20° C

    Note: The relative humidity (RH) must be under or equal to maximum allowed by exporter-importer governments, the products must be transported and stored according to manufacturer's instructions

    Note: Exporting - importing meat and animal byproducts is very complex. e.g. Only a few countries are allowed to import meat and animal byproducts inside the EU

    Note: We do not accept suppliers from regions with disease outbreaks. ( That means if you have disease like Covid, Ebola virus, Swine flu, Mad Cow disease in your region we will not accept any meat or animal origin products from your company, even if your government tells us there is no problem, we must verify. )

    Note: For all products in this category you must have documents that you raised, feed, slaughter, proccesed the animals according to international food safety - food hygiene - biosecurity standards. The animals can be slaughter according to the importer's country food safety laws or the client company must send their own butchers to slaughter the animals according to their religios believes e.g. Kosher, Halal and so on. Universal Declaration of Human Rights Article 18 - Everyone has the right to freedom of thought, conscience and religion.

    Note: We do not accept meat from sick or infected animals, animals allowed to eat garbage, abused or bruised or injured animals, newly born, pregnant animals, animals with high fat deposits, stressed animals, not well rested animals during the 24-hour period before slaughter, animals handled with electric prodders, animals living in unhygienic and overcrowded conditions, live animals not transported in clean-disinfected-washed-ventilated specialized vehicles, live animals transported in overcrowded vehicles, live animals transported more then 50-100km from place of origin.

    Note: The meat must be washed only with potable water, the meat should not have blood marks and must be clean, the meat must not have any foreign smell, the meat must not have broken bones, the meat must not be bruised, the meat must not be discolored, the meat must have characteristic color and so on, the meat must have the mandatory food safety and legal documents according to the international legislation and national legislation of each country.

    Note: Suppliers must eviscerate and clean the products with potable water, before they put them on scale to be weighted. They will not be payed for the eviscerated content - impurities.

    Note: Suppliers must have contracts with authorised companies to buy and/or to dispose the eviscerated content - impurities.

    Note: Suppliers must have documents evidence that the products do not contain antibiotics, parasites - pathogens, heavy metals, toxic chemicals.

    Note: Suppliers must have documents evidence that the products are not radioactive and that they do not come from contaminated areas like Chernobyl.

    Note: The products must be graded according to importer's country legislation and client needs.

    Note: Suppliers are not allowed to mix fresh products with old and/or spoiled products. ( Suppliers must have documents evidence that the products are from today's catch, not from last week, that also means do not stock products until we have signed permission from clients to go at sea to capture the products. )

    Note: Meat is considered a biological weapon. Before we release any payment for these products, we want the legal representative of the supplier, his wife, his kids and his family to cook and eat a meat sample from the same lot that is shipped to clients around the world.

    Note: Suppliers must have documents evidence that the products are captured in season and not in time of fishing prohibition.

    Note: Suppliers must have documents evidence that they are allowed to capture the products and that they are not overfishing in international waters ( e.g. proof you didn't steal the fish from other countries territorial waters )

    Note: Suppliers must have documents evidence that the tools they used to capture the products are legal and sustainable.

    Note: Suppliers must have documents evidence that the water in the area where they captured - farmed the products is clean with zero pollution. ( No matter if the products come from fishing or aquaculture )

    Note: Suppliers must have documents evidence that the ice used to keep the products cold comes from potable water that is clean without any impurities.

    Note: Suppliers should use fishing boats without engines where possible. Trawling, poisons, dynamite, nets and traps is not sustainable.

    Note: Fresh products on ice can not be transported very far. You have a few days window to freeze them, eat them or to preserve them.

    Note: Buy the fishing products only if you really need them or for special occasions.

    Note: Suppliers must go at sea only when there is clear sky and sunny, depending on FAO region where they fish. ( Beaufort scale )

    Note: Suppliers must specify how to prepare, fillet, cook and eat the products.

    Note: Fish and seafood legal size, stocks and status will be checked before the contracts are signed. ( Laws, rules and regulations change all the time, today a product's legal size limit can be 25cm+, tomorrow 45cm+ and after tomorrow it can be on the endangered species list and so on. Imagine we are on a spaceship called Earth that is traveling in space. For the spaceship to reach it's destination we must use our resources wisely, else future generations will have nothing to eat. )

    Note: Suppliers must specify the level of glaze and the weight of fish before and after freezing.

    * goods of group 042 (Fish live, fresh or chilled for human consumption) or * goods of group 212 (Prepared and preserved fish, crustaceans, molluscs and other aquatic invertebrates)

    61225 - Wholesale trade services on a fee or contract basis, of sugar and confectionery products Open
    Download as PDF

    Note: For all products in this section, your company has to send the technical specs / quality parameters

    Note: Your company must be authorized to buy these products. ( We do not accept requests from speculators )

    Note: Suppliers must have accredited laboratory test results as proof of safety issued by authorized government agencies for all products. ( Private laboratory test results are not accepted. If the products are poisoned intentionally, it's an act of war ! )

    Note: Suppliers for products in this section must be authorized by food safety organizations, they must have proof of HACCP plan or HACCP accredited certificate

    Note: Products in this section must be packaged according to food safety standards in recyclable or biodegradable food grade packaging

    Note: Frozen* means between -20 and -18° C, Cold* means between 2 and 4° C, Cool* means between 8 and 15° C, Room temperature* means between 15 and 20° C

    Note: The relative humidity (RH) must be under or equal to maximum allowed by exporter-importer governments, the products must be transported and stored according to manufacturer's instructions

    Note: Suppliers must understand very well the concept of clean room, a sugar factory is a great environment for pathogens.

    Note: For group [ 236 ], the clients must specify exactly the product shape, ingredients and filling suppliers should use. Check confectionery and chocolatier books for more info.

    Note: For group [ 236 ], the products must not contain additives and/or toxic chemicals, all aromas-flavors-colorants must be natural.

    Note: The client company will probably want to import these products if energy and labour costs are very high in his country.

    Note: These products are considered bio weapons, it's going to be very difficult to export.

    * goods of group 235 (Sugar and molasses)

    170199 - Sugars; sucrose, chemically pure, in solid form, not containing added flavouring or colouring matter

    BSEI-170199-0001 Room temperature* - Refined white sugar - From sugar beet - polarimeter reading greater than > 99.7° - ICUMSA 45 color ( Beta vulgaris )

    BSEI-170199-0002 Room temperature* - Refined white sugar - From sugar cane - polarimeter reading greater than > 99.7° - ICUMSA 45 color ( Saccharum officinarum )

    Explanatory note for BSEI-170199: Client company must specify sugar crystal size. The fresh sugar will be made according to Standard CXS 212-1999. The supplier must not add ingredients and/or additives. ( e.g. caramel colorant )

    170310 - Sugars; molasses, from sugar cane, resulting from the extraction or refining of sugar

    BSEI-170310-0001 Room temperature* - Molasses - From sugar beet - Sugars greater than > 46% and Brix between 80 - 85° - not for human consumption ( Beta vulgaris )

    170390 - Sugars; molasses, from sugar beet, resulting from the extraction or refining of sugar

    BSEI-170390-0001 Room temperature* - Molasses - From sugar cane - Sugars greater than > 48% and Brix between 80 - 85° - not for human consumption ( Saccharum officinarum )

    Explanatory note for BSEI-170310, BSEI-170390: The supplier must not add ingredients and/or additives.

    180310 - Cocoa; paste, not defatted

    BSEI-180310-0001 Room temperature* - Cacao Liquor - not defatted

    180400 - Cocoa; butter, fat and oil

    BSEI-180400-0001 Room temperature* - Cocoa Butter - [ free fatty acid content expressed as oleic acid less than ≤ 1.75% m/m ] - [ unsaponifiable matter less than ≤ 0.7% m/m ]

    BSEI-180400-0002 Room temperature* - Press Cocoa Butter - [ free fatty acid content expressed as oleic acid less than ≤ 1.75% m/m ] - [ unsaponifiable matter less than ≤ 0.35% m/m ]

    Explanatory note for BSEI-180400: These products must be made according to Standard CXS 86-1981. The packaging must prevent moisture and contact with air. The products must not contain any other ingredients. Hexane and/or methanol is not allowed as processing aid.

    180500 - Cocoa; powder, not containing added sugar or other sweetening matter

    BSEI-180500-0001 Room temperature* - Cacao Powder - cocoa butter content > 20% m/m

    BSEI-180500-0002 Room temperature* - Fat-Reduced Cocoa Powder - cocoa butter content between 10 - 20% m/m

    BSEI-180500-0003 Room temperature* - Highly Fat-Reduced Cocoa Powder - cocoa butter content < 10% m/m

    Explanatory note for BSEI-180500: These products must be made according to Standard CXS 105 - 1981. The packaging must prevent moisture and contact with air. Cacao powder is made from cacao cake. The products must not contain any other ingredients, that means also no additives like Lecithin or Sodium Carbonate or Potassium carbonate and so on.

If you own a boat, yacht, cruise or other marine vessel send proof you can collect and sort the plastic, carton and glass at sea.

    Note: At this moment in time, according to Romanian government decision no. 1074/2021 all S.G.R. packaging has a 0.5 RON tax, when we send the products from Romania or from other countries that have a similiar tax to your company, you have the bear the cost of this tax. It's a tax that importers-buyers can not recover. ( e.g. You can not send back on the territory of Romania waste to recover this tax, it is forbbiden by law. This type of tax is also in Germany, U.S.A. and other countries. )

    Note: The sand is called a concentrate. The grain in the sand is a mineral.

    Note: Countries do not want to export ores-concentrates, they want to process the raw materials and sell you the finite product.

    Note: To check ore or concentrate quality you need to do your own laboratory analysis, there is no other way.

    Note: Suppliers must make sure the products are dry with minimum or no water content.

    Note: Concentrates-ores and semifinished products will be sent to locations where the manufacturing cost is cheaper.     Alloy steels for BSEI-722410, BSEI-722490 include:

    1. Alloy engineering and structural steels usually containing the following elements : chromium, manganese, molybdenum, nickel, silicon and vanadium.

    2. Alloy steels having improved tensile strength and welding properties containing in particular very small quantities of boron (0.0008 % or more by weight) or of niobium (0.06 % or more by weight).

    3. Alloy steels, containing chromium or copper, which are weather resistant.

    4. Alloy steels for so-called “magnetic” sheets (having a low magnetic loss) generally containing 3 to 4 % of silicon and possibly aluminium.

    5. Free-cutting alloy steels which not only conform to the requirements of Note 1 (f) but also contain at least one of the following elements : lead, sulphur, selenium, tellurium or bismuth.

    6. Alloy bearing steels (generally containing chromium).

    7. Alloy manganese silicon spring steels (containing manganese, silicon and possibly chromium or molybdenum) and other alloy steels for springs.

    8. Non-magnetic alloy steels resistant to shock and abrasion, having a high manganese content.

    9. High speed steels : alloy steels containing, with or without other alloy elements, at least two of the three elements molybdenum, tungsten and vanadium with a combined content by weight of 7 % or more, 0.6 % or more of carbon and 3 to 6 % of chromium.

    10. Non-distorting tool steels : containing generally by weight 12 % or more of chromium and 2 % or more of carbon.

    11. Other alloy tool steels.

    12. Permanent magnet steels containing aluminium, nickel, and cobalt.

    13. Non-magnetic alloy steels which are characterised by their manganese or nickel content.

    14. Steels for control rods in nuclear reactors (with high boron content).

    15. Hollow drill bars and rods, of alloy steel.

    You need to do laboratory analysis to determine a chemical composition, each country has it's own standard, we are not payed to monitor all the standards in the world. The alloy steel should not be a stainless steel and it must be according to "3.2.3 Other alloy steel" of EN 10020. Some alloy steels are very complex materials that need a lot of energy to process, make sure you have cheap energy, the proper machinery, equipment and skilled labour before you buy these products.

    The client company must send rebar ribs pattern: smooth, spiral, herringbone or crescend shape ( if possible send picture so no confusion - countries have different standards )

    The client company must send rebar seismic zone where it will be used: e.g. Japan, Tokyo ( High seismic risk ! )

    The client company must send rebar corrosive environment where it will be used: Medium ( Coastal / Industrial )

    The client company must send rebar structure type where it will be used: Bridge, Skyscraper, Tunnel and so on

    The client company must send rebar mechanical properties: elongation, yield strength, tensile load and so on

    The client company must send type of rough coating - intended solely to protect products from rust or other oxidation, to prevent slipping during transport and to facilitate handling: e.g., paints containing an active anti-rust pigment for example, red lead, zinc powder, zinc oxide, zinc chromate, iron oxide (iron minium, jewellers’ rouge), and non-pigmented coatings with a basis of oil, grease, wax, paraffin wax, graphite, tar or bitumen

    The client company must send rebar diameter: 6, 8, 10, 12, 13, 14, 16, 20, 22, 25, 30, 32, 40 or 50mm and so on

    The client company must send rebar grade: e.g. B500C, B500B or B500A and so on

    The client company must send rebar length: cut to size - max 12m

    The client company must send rebar alloy chemical composition e.g. C 0.17 Si 0.4 Mn 0.5 P 0.015 S 0.035 Cr 0.8 Mo 0.2

    The client company must send as much info as possible, your engineer will know what tehnical specs to send.

    Warning ! Do not buy rebar designed for low seismic areas so you can use them in high seismic areas, we do not accept this types of requests.

According to Standard EN 10079 - hot rolled uncoated flat products are products that received just a simple coating for protection against corrosion ar mechanical damage [ e.g. passivation, organic coatings, paper, oil, lacquer etc ] and they are manufactured by hot rolling semi finished products [ blooms or billets or slabs ]. Steel pickling means a treatment with acids to remove impurities, rust, and scale from the surface of the material. They are low quality and cheaper then cold rolled flat products.

    Alloy steels for BSEI-722511, BSEI-722519, BSEI-722530, BSEI-722540, BSEI-722550, BSEI-722591, BSEI-722592, BSEI-722599, BSEI-722611, BSEI-722619, BSEI-722620, BSEI-722710, BSEI-722810, BSEI-722830, BSEI-722850, BSEI-722870, BSEI-722990 include:

    1. Alloy engineering and structural steels usually containing the following elements : chromium, manganese, molybdenum, nickel, silicon and vanadium.

    2. Alloy steels having improved tensile strength and welding properties containing in particular very small quantities of boron (0.0008 % or more by weight) or of niobium (0.06 % or more by weight).

    3. Alloy steels, containing chromium or copper, which are weather resistant.

    4. Alloy steels for so-called “magnetic” sheets (having a low magnetic loss) generally containing 3 to 4 % of silicon and possibly aluminium.

    5. Free-cutting alloy steels which not only conform to the requirements of Note 1 (f) but also contain at least one of the following elements : lead, sulphur, selenium, tellurium or bismuth.

    6. Alloy bearing steels (generally containing chromium).

    7. Alloy manganese silicon spring steels (containing manganese, silicon and possibly chromium or molybdenum) and other alloy steels for springs.

    8. Non-magnetic alloy steels resistant to shock and abrasion, having a high manganese content.

    9. High speed steels : alloy steels containing, with or without other alloy elements, at least two of the three elements molybdenum, tungsten and vanadium with a combined content by weight of 7 % or more, 0.6 % or more of carbon and 3 to 6 % of chromium.

    10. Non-distorting tool steels : containing generally by weight 12 % or more of chromium and 2 % or more of carbon.

    11. Other alloy tool steels.

    12. Permanent magnet steels containing aluminium, nickel, and cobalt.

    13. Non-magnetic alloy steels which are characterised by their manganese or nickel content.

    14. Steels for control rods in nuclear reactors (with high boron content).

    15. Hollow drill bars and rods, of alloy steel.

    You need to do laboratory analysis to determine a chemical composition, each country has it's own standard, we are not payed to monitor all the standards in the world. The alloy steel should not be a stainless steel and it must be according to "3.2.3 Other alloy steel" of EN 10020. Some alloy steels are very complex materials that need a lot of energy to process, make sure you have cheap energy, the proper machinery, equipment and skilled labour before you buy these products.

    61272 - Wholesale trade services on a fee or contract basis, of fertilizers and agrochemical products Open
    Download as PDF

    Note: For all products in this section, your company has to send the technical specs / quality parameters

    Note: Your company must be authorized to buy these products. ( We do not accept requests from speculators )

    Note: Exporting - importing meat and animal byproducts is very complex. e.g. Only a few countries are allowed to import meat and animal byproducts inside the EU

    Note: We do not accept suppliers from regions with disease outbreaks. ( That means if you have diseases like Covid, Ebola virus, Swine flu, Mad Cow disease in your region we will not accept any meat or animal origin products from your company, even if your government tells us there is no problem, we must verify. )

    Note: We have to figure out a way to send to you. Mostly farmers have the logistics to transport manure. Manure contains impurities, farmers will not waste energy to remove them.

    Note: Manure is a animal by-product, it must comply with EU and national legislation of each country, even in transit.

    Note: The manure will not be sanitized ( heat treatment of at least 70°C for min. 1 hour ).

    Note: As client you will have to pay for mandatory microbiological and chemical laboratory analysis.

    Note: Some countries can refuse the manure without any justification. Verify if your country allows manure to be imported.

    Note: These products are considered bio weapons, it's going to be very difficult to export.

    Note: Carpets are used in low traffic areas, they are works of art, they have high quality and they are very expensive

    Note: Rugs are used in medium traffic areas like your home but they use them in churches and mosques also

    Note: Handmade rugs and carpets are more energy efficient, they last longer and they are easier to clean !

    Note: Knotted carpets - are composed of a taut warp around which the pile threads are knotted or twisted in a complete turn round at least one warp thread, the pile threads being kept in place by the insertion of tightly woven weft threads.

    Note: Non-Knotted - means carpets in which the pile threads are simply looped under the warp threads without making a turn round them

    Note: Suppliers must not use any azo dyes or toxic chemicals

    Note: Suppliers must provide instruction how to clean-wash the door mats, rugs and carpets

    Note: For all products in this section, your company has to send the technical specs / quality parameters

    Note: Your company must be authorized to buy these products. ( We do not accept requests from speculators )

    Note: These products will be sent to clients without any warranty, you will need to set up your own computer service to repair the products for clients

    Note: Suppliers must send all documents, tehnical dossier, datasheets, inspection certificates, instruction manuals, declarations of conformity and so on

    Note: Suppliers must send documents proof that the products are eco-friendly and energy efficient.

    Note: Suppliers must make the device keyboard layout according to the client company specifications ( Warning each country has it's own standard and keyboard layout ). The keyboard must be durable.

    Note: The parts and modules must be upgradable, compatible, interchangeable and easy to repair.

    Note: The parts and modules must be recyclable.

    Note: The parts and modules must be easy to add-remove from casing.

    Note: The parts, modules and casing must be easy to clean.

    Note: Where possible, the parts and modules must be made form self-healing materials.

    Note: The battery must be removable.

    Note: The products must work plugged, even without a battery.

    Note: The products must have protection against Overheating, Radio Frequency Interference, Radio Jamming, EMP pulses and/or electric - electrostatic discharge and so on.

    Note: The products must be designed so they can be used outdoor in different climate zones ( e.g. Sahara Desert, Jungle, Artic region and so on ).

    Note: Suppliers must disclose if the products has hidden radio jamming, spyware, malware or remote control hardware and/or software. ( We will reverse engineer your product to verify )

    Note: Suppliers must disclose if the products has hidden harmful hardware and/or software ( e.g. screens harmful to the human eyes, screens and soundcards with hidden subliminal messages, exploding ssd drives, hidden components-parts that release toxic gases intentionally and so on )

    Note: Suppliers must disclose if the products has radio transmitters ( e.g. in many countries people need a licence to broadcast via some types of radio transmitters, e.g. ham radio )

    Note: The product ESD protective packaging must be sealed, light, recyclable, it must include instructions how to handle and warnings, it must be eco-friendly, easy to handle and transport, it must protect the product very well.

    Note: After removing the product from package, the package must still be functional so the client can handle and transport to product in the same package if needed.

    Note: The products must include Windows, Mac or a free operating system like Ubuntu Linux or other distros.

    Note: The products must allow the client to install any operating system.

    Note: The products must include hardware diagnostic tools easy to use. The diagnostic tools must specify exactly what parts and modules are broken and it must also offer solutions how to repair or replace the broken parts and modules.

    Note: The products must contain ports that allow the user to connect to other products and quantum computers.

    Note: If the products do not have CE Marking, conformity must be assessed by EU accredited notified bodies according to Regulation (EC) No 765/2008.

    Note: The clients of the companies that buy Alienware or Apple Laptops are affluent ( rich ), they don't care about tariffs

    Note: From 2024 In European Union almost all non-food products, parts, semifinished goods must be according with Regulation (EC) No 2024/1781 ( "Ecodesign Regulation" )

    - EN 303 687 V1.1.1 - 6 GHz WAS/RLAN; Harmonised Standard for access to radio spectrum

The client company must specify the product code [ e.g. BC547 ], Characteristics, Description, Applications, Graphs, Absolute Maximum Ratings [ e.g. AMR max. values according to IEC 60134 ] and any other info so engineers understand what they need to design. The datasheet should show as much information as possible.

    Explanatory note BSEI-854142, BSEI-854143:

    For space solar cells we have to verify with Romanian army and NATO if we are allowed to buy them.

    A space solar cell has military applications also, we will buy them from EU manufacturers only.

    Custom made solar panels are better and more efficient then manufactured in series panels we see on the market. Manufactured in series panels are used for applications where efficiency is not important.

    Custom made solar panels must also be made according to IEC 61730, IEC 61701, IEC 62716, IEC 61730, IEC 60068.

    61241 - Wholesale trade services on a fee or contract basis, of household furniture Open
    Download as PDF

    Note: For all products in this section, your company has to send the technical specs / quality parameters

    Note: Your company must be authorized to buy these products. ( We do not accept requests from speculators )

    Note: Warning ! We must do due diligence for these products to verify if origin is from sustainable sources, even if you have documents.

    Note: For group 381 all wood products must not have Amazon rainforest origin and they must be PEFC and/or FSC certified.

    Note: The suppliers must have documents proof that all leftover chemicals used in manufacturing the products are recyclable. In most countries manufacturers are still dumping chemicals in rivers, lakes or in the oceans.

    Note: Consult an interior designer before you buy furniture

    Note: Client companies must specify if they want sculpted / carved wood products at demand

    Note: Client companies must send info about brand, model, photos, size, rooms photos, colors, datasheets, technical drawings, type of alloys - materials, package and label design. The client company must send as much info as possible.

    Note: Suppliers must send all documents, tehnical dossier, datasheets, safety datasheets, list with all components-parts, inspection certificates, intellectual property documents, how to assemble and where to use instruction manuals, how to clean, wash and take care of product, how to handle, store and transport, warranty, declarations of conformity and so on

    Note: For furniture kits instructions manuals must be easy to read and drawings must be understandable. The kits must made with minium components-parts ( Don't ask people to assemble 50-100 components )

    Note: Furniture packaging must specify visible total number of components-parts

    Note: The furniture must be durable but light. ( e.g. So it's easy for old people to clean their homes or for young people that want to move.

    Note: All components-parts must be recyclable, compatible, interchangeable and easy to repair

    Note: All products must be easy to clean ( e.g. water, juice, food, coffee, urine, blood spills etc )

    Note: The furniture must have weight limits laboratory test results.

    Note: All products in this group will be custom-made according to client's specifications.

    Note: The products will not be accepted if the suppliers use obsolete - improvised equipment and tools.

    Note: Some products need CE Marking, conformity must be assessed by EU accredited notified bodies according to Regulation (EC) No 765/2008.

    Note: The wood and wood products must be according to Regulation (EU) No 995/2010.

    Note: Preferably, the wood should come from accidental sources. ( e.g. lightning strikes, storms, natural disasters etc )

    Note: In European Union the products must also be according with Regulation (EU) 1907/2006 and 2020/878 ( REACH ).

    Note: The products must not contain any toxic chemicals. The wood for furniture must me stained not painted. The wood must be treated with non-toxic products. ( Wood for furniture is a luxury product, you need to highlight the quality of the wood )

    Note: Furniture upholstery filling must be hygienic and treated. The filling must not make the products saggy. The filling must not be toxic or flammable

    Note: The raw materials must be used properly. ( e.g. Do not use wood to make furniture for public use. Coniferous wood has a tendency to crack should be avoided for furniture. )

    Note: Suppliers are not allowed to add any additives or natural pests to deteriorate the products faster. ( e.g. termites, woodworms, carpenter ants and so on. To force people to buy again and again the same low quality products. )

    Note: Client company and supplier workers must have protective clothing and equipment according to international and national legislation.

    Note: From 2024 In European Union almost all non-food products, parts, semifinished goods must be according with Regulation (EC) No 2024/1781 ( "Ecodesign Regulation" )

    61265 - Wholesale trade services on a fee or contract basis, of hardware and hand tools Open
    Download as PDF

    Note: For all products in class [ 4292 ], your company has to send the technical specs / quality parameters

    Note: Your company must be authorized to buy these products. ( We do not accept requests from speculators )

    Note: Client companies must send info about brand, model, photos, size, datasheets, technical drawings, type of alloys, package and label design. The client company must send as much info as possible.

    Note: The products must be mint condition, no scratch, dent, or mark allowed.

    Note: The products must not contain any toxic chemicals.

    Note: Suppliers must send all documents, tehnical dossier, datasheets, inspection certificates, intellectual property documents, how to and where to use instruction manuals, how to clean and take care of product, how to install, how to sharpen, how to handle, store and transport, warranty, declarations of conformity and so on

    Note: All wood products must not have Amazon rainforest origin and they must be PEFC and/or FSC certified.

    Note: Suppliers must specify wood species used to make handles, tools and/or parts.

    Note: All products must be tested before shipping.

    Note: The tools and/or parts must be upgradable, compatible, interchangeable and easy to repair.

    Note: The tools and/or parts must be recyclable.

    Note: The tools and/or parts must be easy to add-remove. ( Imagine your a Formula 1 mechanic in a pit stop )

    Note: The tools and/or parts must withstand corrosion. The tools must be easy to clean.

    Note: The tools and/or parts must be engraved or etched according to client company specifications. The letters, numbers and/or design must not be easy to remove.

    Note: The products must be designed so they can be used outdoor in different climate zones ( e.g. Sahara Desert, Jungle, Artic region and so on ).

    Note: After removing the product from package, the package must still be functional so the client can handle and transport to product in the same package if needed.

    Note: Most metals have dual-use applications, before we can export them we have to verify if they need special export-import licences and so on.

    Note: Client company and supplier workers must have protective clothing and equipment according to international and national legislation.

    Note: The products will not be accepted if the suppliers use obsolete - improvised equipment and tools.

    Note: In European Union some materials used to make this products must be according with Regulation (EU) 1907/2006 and 2020/878 ( REACH )

    Note: In European Union materials and articles that enter in contact with food must be according with Regulation (EC) No 2023/2006

    Note: From 2024 In European Union almost all non-food products, parts, semifinished goods must be according with Regulation (EC) No 2024/1781 ( "Ecodesign Regulation" )

    * goods of class 4292 (Hand tools (including hand tools of a kind used in agriculture, horticulture or forestry, hand saws, files, pliers and metal cutting shears, hand-operated spanners, blow-lamps and clamps); interchangeable tools for hand tools or for machine tools, including dies for drawing or extruding metal, and rock drilling or earth boring tools; knives for machines; plates, sticks, tips and the like for tools, unmounted, of sintered metal carbides or cermets)

    Explanatory note BSEI-820411, BSEI-820412, BSEI-820420:

    [A] [B] [CC] [DD] [E] No. Meaning according to ISO 1703

    A: Group of tools: [ 1: wrenches ], [ 2: sockets ], [ 3: bits ], [ 4: screwdrivers ], [ 5: connecting parts ], [ 6: driving parts ], [ 7: torque tools ]

    B: Hand or machine: [ 1: hand ], [ 2: machine operation; partial hand operation is possible using supplementary tools ]

    CC: Geometrical characteristics of the driven part: [ 00: no driven part ], [ 01: parallel flanks (hexagon, square,...) ], [ 02: external hexagon ], [ 03: internal hexagon ], [ 04: slotted ], [ 05: recessed head PH ], [ 06: recessed head PZ ], [ 07: spline ], [ 08: external square ], [ 09: internal square ], [ 10: triangular external square ], [ 11: triangular internal square ], [ 12: notch ], [ 13: hole ], [ 14: multi-spline ], [ 15: serrations ]

    DD: Serial number

    Option of coating: [ 0: standard ], [ 1: coating for live working under low voltage (IEC 60900) ]

    Client company must specify handle type, handle material e.g. plastic or metal, color, product size, shape and any other useful info. The client can also specify the manufacturing method and the type of material, e.g. product material EN ISO 683-1 steel and its corresponding grade, or Stainless steel etc.

    - No. 208 - Straight fluted tap with spiral point

    - No. 209 - Right hand spiral fluted tap

    - No. 210 - Left hand spiral fluted tap

    - No. 211 - Tap with interrupted threads (there are several designs of interrupted threads)

    - No. 212 - Tandem tap

    - No. 213 - Tap with plain cylindrical pilot

    - No. 214 - Internal centre

    - No. 215 - External centre

    Note: For all products in group [ 261 ], your company has to send the technical specs / quality parameters

    Note: For all products in this group, your company has to send the technical specs / quality parameters

    Note: Your company must be authorized to buy these products. ( We do not accept requests from speculators )

    Note: For all products in this group, suppliers must have animal origin by-products safety documents

    Note: Fibers from cloned animals are not accepted

    Note: Suppliers must have traceability documents for all the products they used to treat the animals for lice, flies, maggots, mites, scab and other parasites.

    Note: Suppliers must have origin documents for all the products. ( e.g. It's forbidden to export goat hair from a region that has Ebola virus epidemic )

    Note: Before we buy the products, we must verify if suppliers use child labor, if they respect work labor laws, if suppliers pay salaries on time and so on.

    Note: Suppliers should use natural non-toxic insect repellents to counter damage from insects. ( e.g. Lavender and/or thyme herbal sachets )

    Note: The client company must specify the grading system, most countries have their own grading methods.

    Note: The fibers must be from the same breeds and it must have same color. No mixed colors and/or breeds and/or crossbreeds fibers are permited. ( Do not mix the fibers ! )

    Note: The fibers must be from same region of the animal. ( e.g. Wool from the belly region of the animal must not be mixed with lower quality wool from around the tail )

    Note: The fibers must have similar length. The suppliers must not mix long fibers with short fibers.

    Note: The suppliers must not try to fake wool, animal hair, silk or other expensive natural fibers. The suppliers must not mix wool with goat hair or dog hair or synthetic fibers and so on.

    Note: Suppliers must not pollute the waters and/or lands with animal fibers even if there is no demand.

    Note: The products must have recyclable protective packaging against heat, sunlight, moisture and insects.

    Note: Suppliers must not brand the animals. The owners should use ear tags.

    Note: The practice of mulesing and treating animals with liquid nitrogen is forbbiden. The animals must not be mistreated. The animals must be well taken care of.

    Note: Wool and animal hair must be shorn.

    Note: Suppliers must be washed and clean when they will shear the animals so they do not contaminate the products. No dogs allowed near the shearing area.

    Note: The animal shearer should sober and professional. No amatures should be allowed to shear the animals. Fibers from wounded animals are not accepted.

    Note: The products must be labeled and packaged / baled according to client company specifications with recyclable and eco-friendly materials.

    Note: All products must be dry, they must have minimum moisture content. ( e.g. To prevent cheating at scale )

    Note: The products must be washed and clean. The products must not be contaminated with smoke, tobacco, foreign smell, thorns, thistles, vegetable matter, seeds, dung, urine, dirt, blood, skin, meat, fat, toxic chemicals, parasites and/or pathogens.

    Note: From 2024 In European Union almost all non-food products, parts, semifinished goods must be according with Regulation (EC) No 2024/1781 ( "Ecodesign Regulation" )

    Explanatory note for BSEI-511111, BSEI-511119, BSEI-511211, BSEI-511219, BSEI-530911, BSEI-530919, BSEI-531010, BSEI-531090, BSEI-531100: For machine-made products the client company must specify:

    IS0 9354 - The weave code if possible according to the coding system

    ISO 3572 - Weave construction

    Optional: ISO 7211-1,2,3,4,5,6 - Woven fabrics — Construction - Methods of analysis

    ISO 1833 - Weave composition

    ISO 13934-1 - The tensile properties

    ISO 4920 - The resistance to surface wetting

    ISO 105 - The resistance of the colour

    EN 12127 - The mass per unit

    ISO 14419 - The fabric oil repellency properties

    ISO 9237 - Permeability of fabrics to air

    ISO 6330 - Domestic washing and drying procedures for textile testing - Washing method

    ISO 5077 - Determination of dimensional change in washing and drying

    ISO 7000 - Graphical symbols that should be used on the label

    ISO 12947-1,2 - Martindale determination of the abrasion resistance of fabrics by the Martindale method

    ISO 6940 + ISO 6941 - Flame Retardancy - each country can have their own standard

    Care labelling system info [ how to - wash, dry, iron, bleach, dry clean - info ]. Each country can have their own care labelling system.

    Oeko-Tex Standard 100 certification class [ e.g. I - Items for babies and infants, II - Items with direct prolonged or large-area skin contact, III - Textiles without or with little skin contact, IV - Furnishing materials for decorative purposes ]

    And any other useful info

    Handmade fabrics are non-standard, very expensive and time consuming.

    A few Silk weaves names, some companies also mix the silk with other fibers or the fabrics can be faked. [ e.g. Damascus, Shantung, Habotai ( Mulberry ), Tussore, Georgette ( type of Crêpe silk ), Moiré, Taffeta, Satin, Faille ]

    In some cases it's recomended to mix the natural fibers with reinforcement fibers, else the fabric would be to weak.

For machine-made products the client company must specify:

    IS0 9354 - The weave code if possible according to the coding system

    ISO 3572 - Weave construction ( Denim or Denim + ISO 2076 elastane = Jeans )

    Optional: ISO 7211-1,2,3,4,5,6 - Woven fabrics — Construction - Methods of analysis

    ISO 1833 - Weave composition

    ISO 13934-1 - The tensile properties

    ISO 4920 - The resistance to surface wetting

    ISO 105 - The resistance of the colour

    EN 12127 - The mass per unit

    ISO 14419 - The fabric oil repellency properties

    ISO 9237 - Permeability of fabrics to air

    ISO 6330 - Domestic washing and drying procedures for textile testing - Washing method

    ISO 5077 - Determination of dimensional change in washing and drying

    ISO 7000 - Graphical symbols that should be used on the label

    ISO 12947-1,2 - Martindale determination of the abrasion resistance of fabrics by the Martindale method

    ISO 6940 + ISO 6941 - Flame Retardancy - each country can have their own standard

    Care labelling system info [ how to - wash, dry, iron, bleach, dry clean - info ]. Each country can have their own care labelling system.

    Oeko-Tex Standard 100 certification class [ e.g. I - Items for babies and infants, II - Items with direct prolonged or large-area skin contact, III - Textiles without or with little skin contact, IV - Furnishing materials for decorative purposes ]

    And any other useful info

    Handmade fabrics are non-standard, very expensive and time consuming.

    A few Cotton weaves names, some companies also mix the cotton with other fibers or the fabrics can be faked. [ e.g. Denim, Gingham, Mull, Waffle, Crêpe cotton, Moiré, Printed cotton, Gauze cotton ]

    In some cases it's recomended to mix the natural fibers with reinforcement fibers, else the fabric would be to weak.

    Note: For all products in this section, your company has to send the technical specs / quality parameters

    Note: Your company must be authorized to buy these products. ( We do not accept requests from speculators )

    Note: Before we buy the products, we must verify if suppliers use child labor, if they respect work labor laws, if suppliers pay salaries on time and so on.

    Note: The products must have recyclable and biodegradable protective packaging against heat, sunlight, moisture and insects.

    Note: The products protective packaging must include also a eco friendly non-toxic desiccant.

    Note: The products protective packaging must allow customs to inspect the products.

    Note: The products must be labeled and packaged according to client company specifications with recyclable and eco-friendly materials.

    Note: All products must be dry, they must have minimum moisture content. ( e.g. To prevent cheating at scale )

    Note: The suppliers must use also recycled fibers where possible.

    Note: The suppliers must not try to fake wool, animal hair, leather, silk or other expensive natural fibers.

    Note: The suppliers must have proof for hand-made products.

    Note: The suppliers must specify if the fabrics contain allergic fibers, chemicals and/or pigments.

    Note: Suppliers must not use azo dyes. ( We will verify if you use azo dyes, don't cheat ! )

    Note: Suppliers must send all documents, tehnical dossier, datasheets, tehnical drawings, inspection certificates, intellectual property documents, how to and where to use instruction manuals, how to wash, waterproof and take care of product, warranty, declarations of conformity and so on

    Note: Prêt-à-porte means casual and/or everyday use shoes.

    Note: Haute couture means unique shoes that are used for special occasions. ( e.g. Expensive elegant custom-made shoes used by Movie Stars, Singers, Bands at Festivals, Parties or Concerts )

    Note: Like clothing the shoes are based on season. Seasons [ Fall - Winter ], [ Spring - Summer ], [ Resort ], [ Pre - Fall ].

    Note: For European Union, personal protective equipment must be made according to Regulation ( EU ) 2016/425 and must have CE Marking

    Note: All products in this group must have labels with shoe sizes for different countries, country of origin, exporter, designed by info, importer and manufacturer info, materials used and symbols, qr code, article and bar code, IAN or EAN code, color transfer info, color, type and style info.

    Note: Labels must include also type of lining, sole, upper

    Note: The sole must withstand friction with hot asphalt and concrete heated by the Sun. The sole must be slip resistant

    Note: The sole must prevent dirt buildup and must be easy to clean.

    Note: Labels must be readable, the text must not be tiny.

    Note: All products must have a label that specifies if they can be washed in the laundry machine or not.

    Note: All products in this group must have insole sock or insock info and sample, the suppliers must specify if the product is not waterproof.

    Note: All products must not be to tight and they need to stretch easy.

    Note: Suppliers must specify the standards used and if the products are casual, industrial, safety, protective or occupational footwear.

    Note: The clients must send foot templates if they need unique products

    Note: The clients must specify if the products are for men and/or women and/or children

    Note: Suppliers must make the sports footwear according to the rules / regulations of each sport. The clients must specify the sport rules for manufacturing the products.

    340111 - Soap and organic surface-active products; in the form of bars, cakes, moulded shapes, and paper, wadding, felt and nonwovens, impregnated, coated or covered with soap or detergent, for toilet use (including medicated products)

    BSEI-340111-0001 Toilet Soap - Solid - Hard ( NaOH ) - Custom shape, color and fragrance - For washing skin

    Explanatory note for BSEI-340111: Toilet solid soap you use it to wash your body.

    a) Floating soap - it's used when you wash your body in rivers, ponds, oceans, sea or lakes, they float in water, they don't sink

    b) Deodorant soap - it's a soap that cleans the skin and also helps with managing body odor.

    c) Glycerin soap - it's a soap used by people that have dry skin.

    d) Medicated soap - it's a soap that contains treatments for different skin problems ( e.g. boric acid, salicylic acid, sulphur, sulphonamides or other medicinal substances ).

    e) Disinfectant soap - it's a soap that has antibacterial properties ( it must not contain phenol, cresol, naphthol, formaldehyde or other bactericidal, bacteriostatic, etc., substances that are harmful to humans, animals and/or plants )

    f) Abrasive soap - it's a soap used by people to remove grease and other heavy dirt from the skin. ( e.g. sand, silica, pumice powder, slate powder, sawdust or any similar product is added. )

    The client must send the package and label design. The client company must send as much info as possible about ingredients, the color, product shape, product fragrance. The client company must specify type of toilet solid soap he needs e.g. a), b), c), d), e), f)

    Note: For all products in this section, your company has to send the technical specs / quality parameters

    Note: Your company must be authorized to buy these products. ( We do not accept requests from speculators )

    Note: Suppliers must have accredited laboratory test results as proof of safety and quality.

    Note: Client companies must send info about brand, model, photos, size, datasheets, technical drawings, type of alloys, jewels, glass, package and label design. The client company must send as much info as possible.

    Note: The products must be mint condition, no scratch, dent, or mark allowed. The products must pe ORIGINAL and symmetrical !

    Note: Suppliers must send all documents, tehnical dossier, datasheets, inspection certificates, intellectual property documents, how to and where to use instruction manuals, how to clean and take care of product, how to handle, store and transport, warranty, declarations of conformity and so on

    Note: Suppliers must suggest when after-sales servicing should be done. They must send list or map with authorized service providers.

    Note: Wrist-watches must be fully serviced and must have a certificate of authenticity / certificate of origin / certificate of chronometer ( COSC ) etc

    Note: We don't work with precious metals or precious metals products ( Most suppliers don't have accredited laboratory test results for precious metals )

    Note: Clients that need luxury products know exactly what they want to buy

    Note: Suppliers must have laboratory test results for all parts used to manufacture the products, low quality parts are not accepted. ( e.g. Springs made from music wire )

    Note: From 2024 In European Union almost all non-food products, parts, semifinished goods must be according with Regulation (EC) No 2024/1781 ( "Ecodesign Regulation" )

    Note: The client company must pay all expenses for the armed escorts and undercover intelligence that will accompany the shipment. Once you sign the handover documets, when the products arrive at your location, the armed escorts and undercover intelligence will complete their mission and your security team will be responsible for storage and safety of the products.
