    Note: For group 321 all products must not have Amazon rainforest origin and they must be PEFC and/or FSC certified.

    Note: Suppliers are not allowed to add any additives to deteriorate the products faster. ( To force people to buy again and again the same low quality products. )

    Note: According to Harmonized Tariff Nomenclature explanatory note, pulp is generally presented in baled sheets (whether or not perforated), wet or dry, but may sometimes be in slabs, in rolls or in the form of powder or flakes.

    Note: The suppliers must have documents proof that all leftover chemicals used in manufacturing the products are recyclable. In most countries manufacturers are still dumping chemicals in rivers, lakes or in the oceans.

    Note: Suppliers of wood pulp must have their own clean renewable energy power plants.

    Note: From 2024 In European Union almost all non-food products, parts, semifinished goods must be according with Regulation (EC) No 2024/1781 ( "Ecodesign Regulation" )

    The products must not contain any toxic chemicals.

    * goods of group 321 (Pulp, paper and paperboard), except of subclass 32194

    Explanatory note BSEI-470100: The client company can specify the type of hardwood and/or softwood the manufacturer should use. GWP is also very low quality pulp. ]

    Letter 1 sent to Romania Food Safety Agency - DSVSA Vrancea - 18.05.2023

    Legal Answer to Letter 1 sent by Romania Food Safety Agency - DSVSA Vrancea 8676 - 07.06.2023

    Letter 2 sent to Romania Food Safety Agency - DSVSA Vrancea - 25.04.2025

    After two years of searching the very birocratic romanian legislation system, we found out the Romanian food safety agency lied to us in the legal answer 8676 / 07.06.2023, we found out we need authorization for Fodder ( Animal food products not for human use ). If your company needs fodder from Romania you need to pay the fodder authorization, else we will buy fodder from other countries. If you are a Romanian company that needs fodder from other countries you will have to pay the fodder authorization.

    Legal Answer to Letter 2 sent by Romania Food Safety Agency - DSVSA Vrancea 6278 Part 1- 05.05.2025
    Legal Answer to Letter 2 sent by Romania Food Safety Agency - DSVSA Vrancea 6278 Part 2- 05.05.2025

    Offline methods we can use to Connect

    Method A

    If a supplier or client company needs to send us a msg via radio BLUE SEA EXPORT IMPORT S.R.L. can listen via WebSDR or KiwiSDR

    This method can be used when internet is very expenive in your area.

    Step 1. When you visit the website and when you download the catalog blueseaexportimport.com note down our email, postal address and phone number.

    Step 2. Verify if the weather is clear sky when you want to send radio messages ( minimum interference - it also helps with bouncing radio waves off the ionosphere )

    Step 3. Make sure the message is repeated a few times, so we have time to record it or write it down.

    Step 5. At the end of the message specify how should we contact you back to confirm that we undertand the messages: e.g. email or phone call or SMS

    - Note: In the message include the date and time when we should listen the next message: e.g. 10 September 2025 between 10:30 - 10:55 AM - New York (NY) Local time ( second msg )

    Step 6. Send experimental messages or buy radio ads to verify if you can hear the radio messages on WebSDR or KiwiSDR

    Step 7. Send to us copies of your public document via letter and include:

    - Your company public phone number and company public email e.g. 1 555 533 5135 - email@companyname.org

    - The Public SDR link: e.g. http://websdr.k3fef.com:8901

    - The Broadcast Frequency e.g. 1110.00 kHz

    - The Radio Broadcast Band Name: e.g. AM ( Amplitude modulation )

    - Specify the date and time when we should listen the first message: e.g. 03 September 2025 between 10:30 - 10:55 AM - New York (NY) Local time ( first msg )

    Step 8. If we understand the message we will contact you back as soon as possible via the method you specified.

    Step 9. Anyone can say they are BLUE SEA EXPORT IMPORT S.R.L., when we contact you back, check if it is the same email or phone number noted down in Step 1.



    Method B

    This methods we can used when there is no internet or phone coverage in your area

    Most people read newspapers online, it's no longer a good way to connect offline via classified ads

    Example: In Kiribati people do not have access to internet or phone service

    1. We can send letters ( your company must pay the cost and fees )

    2. We can place Ads on Radio Stations ( your company must pay the cost - fees)

    3. We can also try to find air cargo companies to airdrop flyers if needed ( your company must pay the cost and fees )

    4. There is also Starlink, Satellite Phone and SSB Radio, this methods are not cheap, you should check the prices.


    Note: The radios in this list are just a guide, they can be shutdown if political regimes change, we do not guarantee that they will accept to broadcast any Ads.

    About us and what we do

    About Us

    BLUE SEA EXPORT IMPORT S.R.L. is a young company registered on 14 February 2023 in Focșani, Romania O.N.R.C. registry with C.U.I. 47626664 and REG. Com. no.: J39/124/2023, managed by Alin Cătălin Tănase


    What We Do ?

    Commodities and goods brokerage / Goods distribution / Export - import and wholesale auctions at request


    BLUE SEA EXPORT IMPORT SRL Commission Contract Services for 10% out of total costs

    A. Brokerage

    - We contact suppliers around the world and request best prices for products you need

    - We verify if products have all documents and we select the best offer from suppliers around the world

    - We escrow for clients


    B. Suppliers scouting and market research

    - We scout routes

    - We make first contact with companies - people around the world

    - We do market research, due diligence and corporate intelligence at client request

    - We verify suppliers public documents ( We check if documents are real or fake )

    - We verify suppliers employees diplomas, hygiene certificates and other proof of skills documents ( We request info from schools where people graduated and ask if documents are real or fake ) at client request

    - We open - close bank accounts and companies at client request

    - We request legal info from authorities when needed

    - We hire service providers temporarily ( e.g. refueling, products parachuting, farmers, fruits pickers, customs brokers, fumigators, translators, lawyers, carriers, logistics, insurance, security, creative people, artists, designers, repair, maintenance and installation service providers etc )

    - We buy or rent tools, labels, pallets, packaging materials and other products at client request

    - We do materials research and development at client request


    C. Monitoring and communications

    - We verify if suppliers respect contract clauses and if they collaborate with the competition to sabotage the clients

    - We track the goods via GPS or/and undercover from point A to point B, we also alert authorities in case of emergency

    - We monitor the manufacturing process and we do random parallel quality control rechecks and counts

    - We ship samples when needed

    - We help with communications setup in remote areas ( satellite internet and phone, radio, wi-fi etc )

    - We recheck if labels according to importing country legislation at client request

    - We can help with software development and debugging

    - We can help with package and label design

    - We do Counter-AI / Quantum Computing Programming research and development at client request


    D. Storage

    - We rent or buy land, warehousing, archiving space, containers for your company


    E. Documents compliance

    - We help with obtaining import-export licences, certificate of origin, phytosanitary certificate, trademark registration and authorizations at client request

    - We help with products compliance ( e.g. obtaining the right to use CE marking for different products ) at client request

    - We buy services from accredited laboratories and we send samples at client request


    Other custom services that your company may need, you need to ask, all services you need will be added in the commission contract.

    - e.g. Goods distribution and/or Wholesale auctions at request


    Company Policy

    a) BLUE SEA EXPORT IMPORT S.R.L. does not export, import, transport or store products for ex communists Romanian "Securitatea" members that did political police, communist political activists, racists, communist torturers or ex legionaries - iron guard or supporters or any other type of extremists;


    b) BLUE SEA EXPORT IMPORT S.R.L. does not export, import, transport or store products from armed conflict zones, we do not work with dictators, war criminals, terrorists, corrupt officials and government clerks, criminal enterprises, gangs, cartels and organized crime syndicates;


    c) BLUE SEA EXPORT IMPORT S.R.L. does not export, import, transport or store tobacco, hunting articles, guns, ammo, drinking alcohol, aerosol spray paints, hemp, hemp seeds, plants or mushrooms that are toxic, prohibited substances, drinks, snacks and sweets that contain banned additives, pirated software, propaganda and indecent materials-prints or printed paper;


    d) BLUE SEA EXPORT IMPORT S.R.L. does not export, import, transport or store wood logs or wood products that are not FSC and/or PEFC certified , even if you are certified, as supplier company must send proof the products come from sustainable exploitation of forests;


    e) BLUE SEA EXPORT IMPORT S.R.L. does not export, import, transport or store products for any company or organization involved in slavery ( forced labor ), child labor and human trafficking or that allows workers to work without safety equipment;


    f) BLUE SEA EXPORT IMPORT S.R.L. does not export, import, transport religious items, some people are experts at manipulating belief systems for person interest.( e.g. People that want "donations" for performing fake miracles );


    g) BLUE SEA EXPORT IMPORT S.R.L. has the right to refuse people who use indecent language, people that try to make a scandal, people under the influence of alcohol or other psychoactive substances, people who break the law or people that incite to break the law;


    h) BLUE SEA EXPORT IMPORT S.R.L. does not request financing - loans or investments from anyone, and it does not offer financing - loans to any entities or private person;


    i) BLUE SEA EXPORT IMPORT S.R.L. does not accept payment via cash, we accept and send payments via TT / Money Order ( Bank Transfer ) only, so we can prevent and combat money laundering;


    j) BLUE SEA EXPORT IMPORT S.R.L. does not participate in market manipulation, gambling - raffle and/or illegal activities;



    Restricted items list, cannot be sent via post and couriers

    Note: The list is just a guide, products can be added or removed from this list - depends on the political and legal system in each country

    - Narcotic plants, mushrooms and substances
    - Weapons, ammo, blunt instruments and sharp objects
    - Explosive substances and devices including fireworks, firecrackers
    - Flammable products and materials ( e.g. fuels, lighters and matches )
    - Toxic substances
    - Irritating substances and paralyzing devices
    - Waste including hazardous waste
    - Smoke screens producing products
    - Counterfeit products
    - Indecent prints and printed paper
    - Propaganda prints and printed paper - it depends on the recipient country
    - Commercial products without a certificate of origin
    - Tools
    - Electronic cigarettes, tobacco, cigarettes and cigars
    - Alcohol and alcoholic drinks
    - Fertilizers
    - Gases (aerosols)
    - Substances with strong odor ( e.g. perfumes, thiols and vinegars )
    - Radioactive products
    - Chemicals, thinners, varnishes, paints, lime and dyes
    - Hazardous substances for the environment
    - Mineral oils and bitumen
    - Biological substances (microbes, viruses, bacteria, parasites and other microorganisms)


    High value and unusual items
    - High value / unusual items
    - Jewellery made with precious metals and stones
    - Watches and clocks
    - Payment instruments ( e.g. banknotes, coins, credit and debit cards )
    - Ivory, minerals, bone, coral, amber and pearls
    - Precious metals and stones
    - Objects with sentimental value
    - Human or animal remains (including ashes)
    - Live animals and humans
    - Batteries and alkaline metals
    - Cement, mortars, slags and ash
    - Items that may damage other packages during transit
    - Fragile items
    - Products made of pewter or tin

    - Resins and saps
    - Animal parts and trophies
    - Products made from fish scales and bones
    - Pet food, fodder and feed
    - Food, salt and perishable goods
    - Fur and fur-lined clothing
    - Vegetable oils, wax, greases, fats
    - Liquids

    Warranty Info

    For products, example electronics and electrical items that we have in catalog we can not give warranty.

    The warranty is valid only in the country where the product is bought.

    For some products that we buy from merchants and producers, we can only open the packages, test them if they are functional before we send them to your company, and we can also ask the suppliers to replace them before we send them to you.

    We will add a clause in the contract that these "products" will be sent to you without warranty

    For some products we will try to find suppliers that offer international warranty.


    Banned Chemicals and Materials

    Banned Synthetic Food Additives

    In our opinion, all synthetic food additives are bad.


    Food additives are chemicals you eat, same as you swallow medicines.


    If you request products that must contain synthetic food additives, we will reject to collaborate with you.



    Regulation (EC) No 1333/2008 of the European Parliament and of the Council of 16 December 2008 on food additives



    Article 3 - Definitions


    (a) ‘food additive’ shall mean any substance not normally consumed as a food in itself and not normally used as a characteristic ingredient of food, whether or not it has nutritive value, the intentional addition of which to food for a technological purpose in the manufacture, processing, preparation, treatment, packaging, transport or storage of such food results, or may be reasonably expected to result, in it or its by-products becoming directly or indirectly a component of such foods;

    The following are not considered to be food additives:

    (i) monosaccharides, disaccharides or oligosaccharides and foods containing these substances used for their sweetening properties;

    (ii) foods, whether dried or in concentrated form, including flavourings incorporated during the manufacturing of compound foods, because of their aromatic, sapid or nutritive properties together with a secondary colouring effect;

    (iii) substances used in covering or coating materials, which do not form part of foods and are not intended to be consumed together with those foods;

    (iv) products containing pectin and derived from dried apple pomace or peel of citrus fruits or quinces, or from a mixture of them, by the action of dilute acid followed by partial neutralisation with sodium or potassium salts (liquid pectin);

    (v) chewing gum bases;

    (vi) white or yellow dextrin, roasted or dextrinated starch, starch modified by acid or alkali treatment, bleached starch, physically modified starch and starch treated by amylolitic enzymes;

    (vii) ammonium chloride;

    (viii) blood plasma, edible gelatin, protein hydrolysates and their salts, milk protein and gluten;

    (ix) amino acids and their salts other than glutamic acid, glycine, cysteine and cystine and their salts having no technological function;

    (x) caseinates and casein;

    (xi) inulin;


    (b) ‘processing aid’ shall mean any substance which:

    (i) is not consumed as a food by itself;

    (ii) is intentionally used in the processing of raw materials, foods or their ingredients, to fulfil a certain technological purpose during treatment or processing; and

    (iii) may result in the unintentional but technically unavoidable presence in the final product of residues of the substance or its derivatives provided they do not present any health risk and do not have any technological effect on the final product;


    (c) ‘functional class’ shall mean one of the categories set out in Annex I based on the technological function a food additive exerts in the foodstuff;


    (d) ‘unprocessed food’ shall mean a food which has not undergone any treatment resulting in a substantial change in the original state of the food, for which purpose the following in particular are not regarded as resulting in substantial change: dividing, parting, severing, boning, mincing, skinning, paring, peeling, grinding, cutting, cleaning, trimming, deep-freezing, freezing, chilling, milling, husking, packing or unpacking;


    (e) ‘food with no added sugars’ shall mean a food without the following:

    (i) any added monosaccharides or disaccharides;

    (ii) any added food containing monosaccharides or disaccharides which is used for its sweetening properties;


    (f) ‘energy-reduced food’ shall mean a food with an energy value reduced by at least 30 % compared with the original food or a similar product;


    (g) ‘table-top sweeteners’ shall mean preparations of permitted sweeteners, which may contain other food additives and/or food ingredients and which are intended for sale to the final consumer as a substitute for sugars;


    (h) ‘quantum satis’ shall mean that no maximum numerical level is specified and substances shall be used in accordance with good manufacturing practice, at a level not higher than is necessary to achieve the intended purpose and provided the consumer is not misled.


    ANNEX I - Functional classes of food additives in foods and of food additives in food additives and food enzymes

    sweeteners are substances used to impart a sweet taste to foods or in table-top sweeteners;

    colours are substances which add or restore colour in a food, and include natural constituents of foods and natural sources which are normally not consumed as foods as such and not normally used as characteristic ingredients of food. Preparations obtained from foods and other edible natural source materials obtained by physical and/or chemical extraction resulting in a selective extraction of the pigments relative to the nutritive or aromatic constituents are colours within the meaning of this Regulation;

    preservatives are substances which prolong the shelf-life of foods by protecting them against deterioration caused by micro-organisms and/or which protect against growth of pathogenic micro-organisms;

    antioxidants are substances which prolong the shelf-life of foods by protecting them against deterioration caused by oxidation, such as fat rancidity and colour changes;

    carriers are substances used to dissolve, dilute, disperse or otherwise physically modify a food additive or a flavouring, food enzyme, nutrient and/or other substance added for nutritional or physiological purposes to a food without altering its function (and without exerting any technological effect themselves) in order to facilitate its handling, application or use;

    acids are substances which increase the acidity of a foodstuff and/or impart a sour taste to it;

    acidity regulators are substances which alter or control the acidity or alkalinity of a foodstuff;

    anti-caking agents are substances which reduce the tendency of individual particles of a foodstuff to adhere to one another;

    anti-foaming agents are substances which prevent or reduce foaming;

    bulking agents are substances which contribute to the volume of a foodstuff without contributing significantly to its available energy value;

    emulsifiers are substances which make it possible to form or maintain a homogenous mixture of two or more immiscible phases such as oil and water in a foodstuff;

    emulsifying salts are substances which convert proteins contained in cheese into a dispersed form and thereby bring about homogenous distribution of fat and other components;

    firming agents are substances which make or keep tissues of fruit or vegetables firm or crisp, or interact with gelling agents to produce or strengthen a gel;

    flavour enhancers are substances which enhance the existing taste and/or odour of a foodstuff;

    foaming agents are substances which make it possible to form a homogenous dispersion of a gaseous phase in a liquid or solid foodstuff;

    gelling agents are substances which give a foodstuff texture through formation of a gel;

    glazing agents (including lubricants) are substances which, when applied to the external surface of a foodstuff, impart a shiny appearance or provide a protective coating;

    humectants are substances which prevent foods from drying out by counteracting the effect of an atmosphere having a low degree of humidity, or promote the dissolution of a powder in an aqueous medium;

    modified starches are substances obtained by one or more chemical treatments of edible starches, which may have undergone a physical or enzymatic treatment, and may be acid or alkali thinned or bleached;

    packaging gases are gases other than air, introduced into a container before, during or after the placing of a foodstuff in that container;

    propellants are gases other than air which expel a foodstuff from a container;

    raising agents are substances or combinations of substances which liberate gas and thereby increase the volume of a dough or a batter;

    sequestrants are substances which form chemical complexes with metallic ions;

    stabilisers are substances which make it possible to maintain the physico-chemical state of a foodstuff; stabilisers include substances which enable the maintenance of a homogenous dispersion of two or more immiscible substances in a foodstuff, substances which stabilise, retain or intensify colour of a foodstuff and substances which increase the binding capacity of the food, including the formation of cross-links between proteins enabling the binding of food pieces into re-constituted food;

    thickeners are substances which increase the viscosity of a foodstuff;

    flour treatment agents are substances, other than emulsifiers, which are added to flour or dough to improve its baking quality;

    contrast enhancers are substances which, when applied to the external surface of fruit or vegetables following depigmentation of predefined parts (e.g. by laser treatment), help to distinguish these parts from the remaining surface by imparting colour following interaction with certain components of the epidermis."

    Countries for which EU banks want supporting documents

    Banks want legal documents before they allow transactions with companies from countries in this list

    It's just a guide, you will need to contact your bank to see what countries is on their list. Each bank has it's own policy.

    - The contract

    - Invoice / invoices, to cover the value of the transaction

    - Certificate of origin issued by the competent authority of the country (or an equivalent document that certifies both the country of the producer and his company name )

    - Inspection certificates ( e.g. phytosanitary certificate / health - veterinary certificate and so on )

    - Declaration / certificate of conformity with technical documentation proof

    - Laboratory analysis proof that shows the products are safe and according to EU standards

    - Transport documents

    - The banks may request additional information/documents to clarify the purpose and nature of transactions

    Products Recalls

    All Products Recalls we will be put here

    Proof Documents that we payed excise duties to producers in Romania

    All proofs that we payed excise duties to producers in Romania we will be put here. ( For clients who want to buy this type of products )


    Note: Excise duties products we will buy only from Romania and will not be exported outside European Union for now

    Note: We will import coffee with excise duties from other countries outside the EU only if clients request these products./b>
    In the case of excise duties products ( example bioethanol for fuel use ) in Romania the procedure in this moment in time is this:

    1. The producer ( authorized warehouse ) issues a proforma invoice to the Buyer

    2. The buyer pays the excise duties to the producer ( authorized warehouse ) via bank transfer or money order or via other types of bank payment methods and at details he writes "payment product and payment excise duties value x RON"

    3. The producer ( authorized warehouse ) he will also issue proof that the buyer paid the product including the excise duties , if the producer refuses to issue the proof the authorities must be notified immediately

    4. In case of BLUE SEA EXPORT IMPORT S.R.L. we will put all this proofs that excise duties have been payed to the producer ( authorized warehouse ) on our website, so anyone that wishes to see them will see them

    5. If the product is outside Romania, Excise duties will be payed again in the country of destination ( it depends on the legislation of that country ) , after that we must request reimbursement of excise duties from Romania and the money will be returned to the client who payed it, the bank fees will be payed by the client also.

    How to Become a Supplier

    All suppliers and clients must edit and sign the Declaration of Compliance With BLUE SEA EXPORT IMPORT S.R.L. Principles before we do any business.


    To become a supplier you must send us:

    - Declaration of Compliance signed by your company legal representative

    - Document proof that you have legal documents

    - Document proof that the products are safe / high quality.
      Note: All products safety documents must have the exportering country representative agencies stamps. ( e.g. If the food is poisoned intentionally we know exactly what country to blame, we don't accept TUV, Eurofins or other private laboratories test results as safety documents. )

    - Document proof that your products can be repaired and that they have interchangeable parts

    - Document proof that your products can be recycled or that they are biodegradable

    - Document proof that your products do not come from deforested areas

    - Document proof of phytosanitary warning bulletins, phytosanitary shop invoices, plant protection products labels and phytosanitary treatments records.
      Note: Farmers are not allowed to apply phytosanitary treatments without recommendation from local phytosanitary institution, also they need to keep a registry with all treatments they applied to plants. )

    - Document proof that your company is environment friendly

    - Document proof that your company is sustainable

    - Document proof that your company uses renewable energy

    - Document proof that you respect your workers

    - Document proof that you do not steal utilities ( e.g. electricity ) to manufacture products.

    - Document proof that you have production capacity

    - Document proof that you respect intellectual property rights

    - Document proof that you know exactly what allergens are in your products

    - Agreement that you allow us to make public all documents you send

    - Agreement for exclusive rights to buy your products

    - According to Regulation (EU) 2023/988 Article 10 you must appoint by means of a written mandate BLUE SEA EXPORT IMPORT S.R.L. or another company as authorized representative to put products on the EU Market

    - From 2024 In European Union almost all non-food products, parts, semifinished goods must be according with Regulation (EC) No 2024/1781 ( "Ecodesign Regulation" )

    and so on
